cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.PL, cs.RO. 

The paper presents an ALM library of commonsense knowledge about dynamic domains, which is of interest to researchers in the action language, answer-set programming, and natural language understanding communities. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.PL are the most likely categories. The paper also involves natural language understanding, which suggests cs.CL as another possible category. The library can be used for planning, which is related to robotics, hence cs.RO is also a possible category. Finally, the paper involves machine learning, which suggests cs.LG as another possible category.
